# <% .Name %>

A workshop built with [worky](https://github.com/davideimola/worky).

## For participants

### 1. Download the binary

Go to the [releases page](../../releases) and download the binary for your platform.

### 2. Make it executable (macOS / Linux)

```sh
chmod +x ./<% .Slug %>-*
```

> **macOS:** if you see *"cannot be opened because the developer cannot be verified"*, right-click the binary in Finder and choose **Open**, or run:
> ```sh
> xattr -d com.apple.quarantine ./<% .Slug %>-darwin-*
> ```

### 3. Start the workshop

```sh
./<% .Slug %>-<platform> serve --open
```

Your browser will open automatically. Follow along and complete each chapter.

### 4. Validate and progress

```sh
./<% .Slug %>-<platform> check     # run checks and unlock the next chapter
./<% .Slug %>-<platform> status    # see which chapters are complete
./<% .Slug %>-<platform> reset     # start over from the beginning
```

---

## For workshop creators

### Prerequisites

- Go 1.24+

### Setup

```sh
go mod tidy
```

### Development

```sh
make serve    # run the workshop locally
make check    # check current chapter progress
make status   # show all chapter statuses
make reset    # reset progress
```

### Build and release

```sh
make build    # build for current platform
make release  # cross-compile for all platforms
```

Or push a tag to trigger the GitHub Actions release workflow:

```sh
git tag v1.0.0
git push origin v1.0.0
```

Built with [worky](https://worky.davideimola.dev) — see the docs for configuration, checks, and customization.
